From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] nss_core: fix fraglist skb truesize under-accounting

When the firmware delivers a frame as a multi-segment chain (observed
for virtually every full-MTU frame received through the wifili path),
nss_core_handle_linear_skb() builds a fraglist skb but sets the head's
truesize to desc->payload_len and grows it by desc->payload_len per
appended segment. The result is truesize == exact wire frame length,
which accounts for neither the two full-size receive buffers backing
the chain nor the skb structures themselves.

Before delivery, nss_core_handle_buffer_pkt() linearizes the fraglist
for netdevs without NETIF_F_FRAGLIST (i.e. all of them). The second
segment usually fits the head buffer's tailroom, so __skb_linearize()
succeeds without reallocating the head and the bogus truesize survives
into the network stack. Locally terminated TCP then trips

  WARNING: ... net/core/skbuff.c:6200 skb_try_coalesce+0x4b8/0x504

(WARN_ON_ONCE(delta < len), delta = truesize - SKB_DATA_ALIGN(sizeof
(struct sk_buff))) on the first coalesced segment, and every chained
frame under-accounts socket receive memory by roughly a full buffer.

Keep the allocation-time truesize on the chain head and account each
appended segment with its own full truesize, matching how the kernel
itself accounts fraglists (e.g. IP defrag). Over-accounting after a
later linearize is safe; under-accounting is what the WARN exists to
catch.

The paged/nr-frags path is already correct (it keeps the initial
truesize and skb_add_rx_frag() adds PAGE_SIZE per segment) and is not
touched.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/nss_core.c
+++ b/nss_core.c
@@ -1371,7 +1371,6 @@ static inline bool nss_core_handle_linea
 
 		skb_frag_list_init(nbuf);
 		nbuf->data_len = 0;
-		nbuf->truesize = desc->payload_len;
 		nbuf->priority = desc->pri;
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT
@@ -1431,7 +1430,7 @@ static inline bool nss_core_handle_linea
 	 */
 	head->data_len += desc->payload_len;
 	head->len += desc->payload_len;
-	head->truesize += desc->payload_len;
+	head->truesize += nbuf->truesize;
 
 	if (!(bit_flags & N2H_BIT_FLAG_LAST_SEGMENT)) {
 		/*
